business.name: The Mindful Body Massage
business.description: At The Mindful Body Massage our clients are our top priority. We care about giving you a relaxing and healing experience everytime. We pride ourselves on good commuincation with our clients to ensure that the massage you recieve is tailored to your needs. We offer a several massage options and believe we have something for everyone. Here at The Mindful Body Massage, we combine the power of massage with other alternative healing modalities to give you the best experience possible in your healing journey. We are here and ready to welcome you to your own journey of healing and self love.

services.description: Swedish massage targets the more superficial layers of muscle and consists of light to firm pressure, longer strokes, and smooth gliding movement over the body. Ideal for relaxation and reduction of mild muscle tension from everyday activities.
services.name: Swedish Massage

services.description: A massage that is ideal for more chronic pain and past muscle related injury. Deep tissue massage is used to target deeper into the muscle layers, reduce tendon tightness, and work out pain and stiffness in major muscle groups and around the joints. You can expect prolonged, deep pressure on muscle adhesion and knots and pain that "Hurts so good!"
services.name: Deep Tissue Massage

services.description: Cupping is an ancient technique that originates from China, and has gained popularity in recent years. It is used to help relieve pain and inflammation, promote circulation, increase range of motion, and decompress soft tissue using vacuum suction to decrease muscle tightness. Cupping massage combines push and pull to maximize adhesion release by lifting the tissue with the cupping therapy, and then pressing into the muscle with massage. 90 minutes is required for a full body cupping session. 60 minutes is suitable for upper body only, or focus work on other areas of the body. It is normal to have circular sometimes sensitive cupping marks following a cupping massage. You should avoid cupping if you have any of the following conditions: Anemia, hemophilia (or any other bleeding disorder), blood clotting issues, DVT, a history of strokes, cardiovascular disease, a pace maker, topical skin conditions such as psoriasis and eczema, or epilepsy. After receiving cupping therapy, to maximize the benefits and allow the body to process the treatment to the fullest extent, one should avoid hot showers, hot tubs, saunas, extreme cold, intense exercise, the consumption of caffeine, alcohol, processed or sugary food and drinks, and dairy for 4-6 hours post treatment. Avoiding these things allows your body to give full focus and energy to processing the treatment.
services.name: Cupping Massage

services.description: Hot stone massage uses smooth basalt stones heated to the perfect temperature to help melt away tension and stress. This massage utilizes the heat of the stones to penetrate down into the muscles to help obtain full release and relaxation. The stones can be placed onto the skin directly or on top of a sheet and are heated to a temperature between 110-130 degrees Fahrenheit. Hot stone massage is the perfect way to melt away the worries and stress of life.
services.name: Hot Stone Massage

services.description: Focusing on the head and neck only, this massage uses a combination of gentle touch and deeper scalp massage to promote healing and relaxation in an area of the body that is notorious for holding stress.
services.name: Head and Neck Massage

services.description: By popular request, this massage is a very gentle and light touch that caresses away stress. also known as a back "scratch" or "tickle" often this massage feels very healing to ones inner child and releases internal hurt and stress in a whole new way.
services.name: Gentle Touch Massage

services.description: A soothing Swedish massage modified to be relaxing and safe for you and baby.  We have prenatal bolster pillows for the ability to lie face down, or pillows to prop and position for side laying massage, so you get to choose what position feels safest and most comfortable for you and baby. When booking, please note how far along you are in your pregnancy. We look forward to helping you thank your body for the amazing work its doing.
services.name: Prenatal Massage

business.booking_policy: Changes allowed up to 2 hours before visit
business.deposit_policy:
This business enforces a cancellation policy on and reserves the right to charge a cancellation fee for any no-shows and late cancellations. Note that you may be considered a no-show if you are more than 15 minutes late for your scheduled appointment, and it is up to the business to decide whether the fee is applied.

The cancellation fee is only charged if you violate the terms of the cancellation policy. If you show up to the appointment on time or cancel before the deadline listed on your confirmation page, no cancellation fee is withdrawn from your account. As the fee is not charged for successful appointments, you will be expected to pay for your appointment in full once the service is completed.
